## Hints for Future Agents

- When a stack-root PR merges, the immediate signal is a `feat(...)`
  commit appearing in origin/master with the same message as the root
  PR. Look for it before rebasing — it tells you that `git rebase
  --skip` is the right resolution for the inevitable semconv-style
  duplicate-change conflict.
- `git reset --soft <feat-commit> && git commit --amend --no-edit`
  is a fast way to fold N session checkpoint commits into the
  preceding clean commit before a rebase.
- PR base auto-retargets to the new base when the parent branch is
  deleted (GitHub auto-deletes merged branches in this repo). No
  manual `gh pr edit --base` needed.

## Codebase Discoveries

- `git diff origin/master --stat` is a great sanity-check after a
  rebase that's supposed to collapse a stack: it tells you exactly
  which files the PR now changes vs master. Here it confirmed only
  9 ADK-specific files, 0 noise.

